Origin: DHI-internal (DHI build harness)
Description: Skip sync_default_gems.rb's advisory rubygems.org "latest version"
 check. tool/sync_default_gems.rb calls check_prerelease_version at the start of
 a sync, which does a Net::HTTP.get to rubygems.org purely to print a
 "not latest version" notice. The DHI package builder is hermetic (no network),
 so that call raises Socket::ResolutionError and aborts the sync even though the
 sync itself only copies from the local ../../ruby/<gem> checkout. Returning
 early neutralizes the cosmetic check without affecting the actual sync.
 This variant matches the Ruby 4.0 tool layout.
Forwarded: not-needed (DHI build environment workaround only)

diff --git a/tool/sync_default_gems.rb b/tool/sync_default_gems.rb
index 6945c6c..79a13f5 100644
--- a/tool/sync_default_gems.rb
+++ b/tool/sync_default_gems.rb
@@ -427,6 +427,7 @@ module SyncDefaultGems
   end
 
   def check_prerelease_version(gem)
+    return # DHI: skip rubygems.org prerelease check (no network in hermetic build)
     return if ["rubygems", "mmtk", "cgi", "pathname"].include?(gem)
 
     require "net/https"
